Backend

Class User.GameEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • Backend.User.GameEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Enclosing class:
    User

    public class User.GameEntry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A game entry object is simply an abstraction for a game record. A Game Entry contains essential informatioin of a single series played (best of 3). This would include the opponent name and who won. GameEntry objects are intended to be iterable across an array and comparable with other GameEntry instances.

    The results in GameEntry are intended to be relative to its owning User object. The owning user provides the remaining information (ie. who does the win status belong to, who is the other user who is not the opponent). Therefore, the GameEntry only exists within the context of a User.
